claims:
1. An apparatus, comprising:
a bio-impedance sensor configured to take a bio-impedance measurement from a body of an individual;
an optical sensor configured to take an optical measurement from the body of the individual; and
a processing device coupled to the bio-impedance sensor and the optical sensor, the processing device configured to:
receive a first bio-impedance measurement from the bio-impedance sensor taken during a first period of time;
receive a first optical measurement from the optical sensor taken during the first period of time;
receive first location information of the individual during the first period of time;
determine a first correlation between a physiological parameter and at least one of the first location information, the first bio-impedance measurement, or the first optical measurement;
determine a first level of the physiological parameter based on the first correlation;
determine a second correlation between a hydration parameter of the individual and the bio-impedance measurement;
assign a first weight corresponding to the second correlation;
determine a second correlation between a blood sugar parameter of the individual and the optical measurement;
assign a second weight to the third correlation;
in response to determining a first level of a first physiological condition of the individual based on the first correlation, adjust the first weight corresponding the second correlation;
in response to determining a second level of a second physiological condition of the individual based on the third correlation, adjust the second weight corresponding to the third correlation;
predict individual behavior based on one or more assigned weights; and
display activity to be taken by the individual according the assigned weight prediction.
2. The apparatus of claim 1, wherein the processing device is further configured to:
receive a second bio-impedance measurement from the bio-impedance sensor taken during a second period of time;
receive a second optical measurement from the optical sensor taken during the second period of time;
receive second location information of the individual during the second period of time, wherein the second location information is different than the first location information;
determine a second correlation between the physiological parameter and at least one of the second location information, the second bio-impedance measurement, or the second optical measurement; and
determine a change of the physiological parameter from the first level to a second level based on the first correlation and the second correlation.
3. The apparatus of claim 2, further comprising a location sensor configured to generate the first location information and the second location information.
4. The apparatus of claim 2, wherein the first location information or the second location information is a geographical location of a gym, a residence of the individual, or a place of employment of the individual.
5. The apparatus of claim 2, wherein the first location information or the second location information are accessed from a digital calendar associated with the individual.
6. The apparatus of claim 2, wherein:
the first level of the physiological parameter is determined based on a physical activity scheduled in a digital calendar associated with the individual; and
the second level of the physiological parameter is determined based on a physical activity scheduled in the digital calendar associated with the individual.
7. The apparatus of claim 2, wherein the processing device is further configured to determine that the change of the physiological parameter from the first level to the second level is based on a first physical activity of the individual at a first geographical location and a second physical activity of the individual at a second geographical location.
8. The apparatus of claim 2, wherein the processing device is further configured to:
determine a blood sugar level of the individual is at the first level based on the individual being located at a residence of the individual, the individual being located at the residence being indicative of a decrease in physical activity or eating meals at the residence resulting in an increased blood sugar level; and
determine the blood sugar level of the individual is at the second level based on the individual located at a gym, the individual being located at the gym being indicative of increased physical activity resulting in a decreased blood sugar level.
